rrent_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null,"can_vote":false},{"id":3119150,"name":"Matt","username":"thatmattguy","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/thatmattguy/{size}/222358_2.png","created_at":"2023-01-08T05:29:35.284Z","cooked":"<p>You can reference Photon? Hereâ€™s the Apriltag detector call we actually make. Just give it a greyscale image basically <a href="https://github.com/PhotonVision/photonvision/blob/86b9d4b037faf9c60bf5a66bf5860bc84168a84f/photon-core/src/main/java/org/photonvision/vision/pipe/impl/AprilTagDetectionPipe.java#L45" class="inline-onebox" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">photonvision/AprilTagDetectionPipe.java at 86b9d4b037faf9c60bf5a66bf5860bc84168a84f Â· PhotonVision/photonvision Â· GitHub</a></p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":50,"updated_at":"2023-01-08T05:29:35.284Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":41,"reads":781,"readers_count":780,"score":381.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":421411,"topic_slug":"wpilib-apriltagdetector-sample-code","display_username":"Matt","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/PhotonVision/photonvision/blob/86b9d4b037faf9c60bf5a66bf5860bc84168a84f/photon-core/src/main/java/org/photonvision/vision/pipe/impl/AprilTagDetectionPipe.java#L45","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"photonvision/AprilTagDetectionPipe.java at 86b9d4b037faf9c60bf5a66bf5860bc84168a84f Â· PhotonVision/photonvision Â· GitHub","clicks":675}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":37738,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/wpilib-apriltagdetector-sample-code/421411/2","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3119224,"name":"mikets","username":"mikets","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/mikets/{size}/4625_2.png","created_at":"2023-01-08T06:19:10.149Z","cooked":"<p>I read about Photon. It seems PhotonLib can be run on a PC, the robot or an off-board coprocessor such as Raspberry Pi or Limelight. Is it correct? I assume the link you provided is code for running the pipeline on the robot. Is it correct? How does the performance look like? Is m_detector.detect(in.getMat()) a synchronous call? If so, I should run this pipeline on a separate thread?</p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":50,"updated_at":"2023-01-08T06:19:10.149Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":23,"reads":731,"readers_count":730,"score":271.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":421411,"topic_slug":"wpilib-apriltagdetector-sample-code","display_username":"mikets","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":37738,"username":"thatmattguy","name":"Matt","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/thatmattguy/{size}/222358_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":13461,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/wpilib-apriltagdetector-sample-code/421411/3","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3119230,"name":"Peter Johnson","username":"Peter_Johnson","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/peter_johnson/{size}/10417_2.png","created_at":"2023-01-08T06:21:09.369Z","cooked":"<p>PhotonVision is designed to run on a coprocessor.  Performance on the Rio is definitely going to be a lot worse than performance on a coprocessor.</p>
<p>Yes, the detect() call is synchronous and the pipeline should be run on a separate thread.</p>
<p>We donâ€™t have any examples yet for WPILibâ€“the classes were written only a couple weeks ago.  Essentially the classes are thin wrappers around the <a href="https://github.com/AprilRobotics/apriltag/wiki/AprilTag-User-Guide">AprilRobotics C implementation</a>.</p>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":50,"updated_at":"2023-01-08T06:24:02.093Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":3,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":16,"reads":647,"readers_count":646,"score":214.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":421411,"topic_slug":"wpilib-apriltagdetector-sample-code","display_username":"Peter Johnson","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/AprilRobotics/apriltag/wiki/AprilTag-User-Guide","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"AprilTag User Guide Â· AprilRobotics/apriltag Wiki Â· GitHub","clicks":53}],"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":13461,"username":"mikets","name":"mikets","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/mikets/{size}/4625_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":13575,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Volunteer WPILib Developer, CSA"},"post_url":"/t/wpilib-apriltagdetector-sample-code/421411/4","custom_user_title":"Volunteer WPILib Developer, CSA","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3119243,"name":"mikets","username":"mikets","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/mikets/{size}/4625_2.png","created_at":"2023-01-08T06:35:11.250Z","cooked":"<p>Thanks for the quick response. It sounds like Limelight hasnâ€™t release a downloadable AprilTag pipeline yet and prepâ€™ing a Raspberry Pi may take too long. But we certainly can play with running AprilTag on the Rio while waiting for Limelightâ€™s release?</p>","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"posts_count":50,"updated_at":"2023-01-08T06:35:11.250Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":4,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":5,"reads":575,"readers_count":574,"score":145.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":421411,"topic_slug":"wpilib-apriltagdetector-sample-code","display_username":"mikets","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":13575,"username":"Peter_Johnson","name":"Peter Johnson","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/peter_johnson/{size}/10417_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":13461,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/wpilib-apriltagdetector-sample-code/421411/5","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3119362,"name":"mikets","username":"mikets","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/mikets/{size}/4625_2.png","created_at":"2023-01-08T07:55:50.564Z","cooked":"<p>I am experimenting with running AprilTagDetector on the Rio, but the code is trying to import PhotonVision. I assume I need to install PhotonVision as a vendor lib. If so, where can I find the json for it or download the off-line package for it?</p>","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"posts_count":50,"updated_at":"2023-01-08T07:55:50.564Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":7,"reads":543,"readers_count":542,"score":163.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":421411,"topic_slug":"wpilib-apriltagdetector-sample-code","display_username":"mikets","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":13461,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/wpilib-apriltagdetector-sample-code/421411/6","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3119363,"name":"Dan Katzuv","username":"dan","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/d/eada6e/{size}.png","created_at":"2023-01-08T07:57:02.185Z","cooked":"<p>Limelight has released Limelight 3 yesterday, but older models are expected to support AprilTags too. In the meantime, you can install Photo vision on a Limelight.</p>","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"posts_count":50,"updated_at":"2023-01-08T07:57:02.185Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":5,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":19,"reads":521,"readers_count":520,"score":199.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":421411,"topic_slug":"wpilib-apriltagdetector-sample-code","dis